|---|---|---|
| M1–M2 | `MCTI Schema v0.1`, detector inventory, top-30 snapshot methodology | DIG/YTD outputs published |
| M3–M4 | Signed snapshots, confidence metadata, diff stream, historical state | Alerts consuming diff stream |
| M5–M6 | Reproducibility review + schema review complete | Dashboard, labels, manifest generator |

### Acceptance criteria per deliverable (appendix)
- Reference consumers accepted only if generated from public registry fields and reproducible detector outputs
- Substrate artifacts accepted on: reproducibility from source + onchain state, signature coverage, detector version traceability

### Conflict-of-interest regime
- Disclosed in RFC body, not appendix: specific vaults/assets/protocols team members are exposed to
- 30-day update trigger on material changes
- Recusal from manual overrides, non-canonical commentary, dispute resolutions, detector exceptions for affected assets
- **Independence filter on demand signals:** affiliated feedback labeled, does not count toward adoption milestones

### Demand evidence protocol
- No LOIs required before submission
- Post-submission commitment: proposal does not advance to vote until ≥2 structured feedback conversations completed OR absence publicly explained
