> The primary funded artifact is not a dashboard or a proprietary risk product. It is an open collateral disclosure substrate: `MCTI Schema v0.1`, detector logic, reproducible registry snapshots, and a structural diff stream for covered Morpho vaults. Dashboards, labels, alerts, and curator manifests are reference consumers of this substrate. They demonstrate usability, but the durable public good is the schema, detector library, provenance trail, and historical registry state.

That does not over-specify scope. It just reorders the hierarchy.

