## Finalized Convergent Spec (the delta from v0.4 as posted)

### Core framing
- Title: *Morpho Collateral Transparency Infrastructure — Open Schema and Reference Implementation for Curator Vault Disclosure*
- Primary funded artifact: `MCTI Schema v0.1` + detector library + reproducible signed registry snapshots + canonical structural diff stream
- Dashboards / labels / alerts / manifests: reference consumers of the substrate, subordinate in narrative, budget, and milestones

### Scope definitions (all must be present in RFC body)
- **Covered vault set:** top 30 Morpho vaults by TVL at a Month 1 snapshot published with data source, timestamp, block number, and vault addresses; any vault entering top 10 by same methodology during grant period is added
- **Covered collateral asset:** assets directly accepted as collateral in covered vaults, plus recursively detected dependencies ≥5% of covered-vault TVL exposure, plus any dependency in a circular exposure path
- **Material incident:** exploit / oracle failure / governance mutation / liquidity impairment / liquidation cascade / depeg / collateral failure affecting a covered vault or asset, publicly reported by protocol, curator, oracle provider, security researcher, or Morpho governance participant
- **Vault drop-out rule:** state explicitly whether a vault that falls out of top-30 mid-grant retains coverage. Recommended: yes, through end of grant period, to avoid coverage churn

### Budget (same $120K total, substrate-priced)
- Must include explicit rows for: schema design + governance, detector library + versioning, reproducibility harness, signed snapshot pipeline, diff stream + historical state
- Reference interfaces (dashboard, labels, manifest generator, alerts) grouped as one line, subordinate in amount to the substrate cluster
- **Fix headline:** $110K → $120K OR cut $10K from a line. Non-negotiable.

### Milestones (your table, adopted)
| Period | Substrate Gate | Reference Consumer |
|---|---|---|
| M1–M2 | `MCTI Schema v0.1`, detector inventory, top-30 snapshot methodology | DIG/YTD outputs published |
| M3–M4 | Signed snapshots, confidence metadata, diff stream, historical state | Alerts consuming diff stream |
| M5–M6 | Reproducibility review + schema review complete | Dashboard, labels, manifest generator |

### Acceptance criteria per deliverable (appendix)
- Reference consumers accepted only if generated from public registry fields and reproducible detector outputs
- Substrate artifacts accepted on: reproducibility from source + onchain state, signature coverage, detector version traceability

### Conflict-of-interest regime
- Disclosed in RFC body, not appendix: specific vaults/assets/protocols team members are exposed to
- 30-day update trigger on material changes
- Recusal from manual overrides, non-canonical commentary, dispute resolutions, detector exceptions for affected assets
- **Independence filter on demand signals:** affiliated feedback labeled, does not count toward adoption milestones

### Demand evidence protocol
- No LOIs required before submission
- Post-submission commitment: proposal does not advance to vote until ≥2 structured feedback conversations completed OR absence publicly explained
- Adoption milestone (third-party trial): documented outreach + one independent trial OR public explanation of non-participation

### Operational commitments (six-line block in RFC body)
- Day-1 public repo (code, schemas, docs, issues, CI, reproducibility harness)
- Signed canonical snapshots (content hash, timestamp, block number, detector version, Git commit, Sigma Labs signature)
- Versioned detectors with changelog + deprecation policy
- Confidence enum: `verified` / `inferred` / `partial` / `unknown` / `unsupported`
- Detection Gap Log, scoped to covered vaults/assets
- Canonical instance operated by Sigma Labs through grant + 12 months post-grant, at Sigma Labs' own cost; fallback maintainer process documented

### Schema governance (one paragraph, appendix)
- Schema changes via public PR with rationale
- 14-day public comment for material changes; 7-day for non-material
- Any change requires detector version bump + before/after comparison
- Standardization path (EIP or equivalent) pursued only after ≥1 independent adopter

### Future Work cap
- One paragraph maximum
- No budget numbers, no timeline, no deliverable commitments
- Any quantitative follow-on is a separate RFC judged on Phase 1 evidence
- **Remove the docsend link** or replace with a public preprint; a governance doc should not contain a gated-access marketing funnel

